### Story
I start my PC for the day and the first thing I do is open proc2. There it shows me 3 task lists: "staging", today's date list, yesterday's date list. This reflects how the proc/proc file is currently used. Much like having proc/proc open in emacs, I interact with proc2 entirely through hot keys. The first task in today's list (at the top) is highlighted indicating that's what I should work on first. In addition to emacs style navigation hotkeys, there are also hotkeys to mark the current task as done (and therefore the next undone task becomes the highlighted one). 